channel.title: Wont let me compile?!
channel.description:
Helloo, rite so everytime i try and compile, I click it and the thingy loads up but nothing in it, then an error message pops up with the title "javac.exe-Unable To Locate Componement" and message is This application has failed to start because jli.dll was not found. Re-installing the application may fix this problem.
What does this mean??? can someone please help me!

item.title: Wont let me compile?!
item.dc:creator: @propaganda propaganda
item.description:
@propaganda wrote:

try this
delete everything in ur compiler
the paste this

@echo off if exist "%programfiles%\Java" (call :compile "%programfiles%\Java\") else (goto error) :compile for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe") if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java) if defined p (goto end) :error echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load. "%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe" http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp :end echo Finished! pause exit

worked for me
